               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Taʾammǝra Māryām “Miracles of Mary" (fols. 3ra-183rb)&#xD; I-1a) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 3ra-8rb)&#xD; I-1b) Maṣḥafa
                     śǝrʿāt, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fol. 10ra-14rb)&#xD; I-2) ʾƎsaggǝd
                     laki wa-ʾǝweddǝsaki ... “I worship Thee ...” and hymns (fols. 14rb-15rb)&#xD;
                     I-3a) Introductory exhortation and hymns (fols. 15va-18ra)&#xD; I-3b)
                     Introductory exhortation and hymns (fols. 19r a-20rb)&#xD; I-4) Taʾammǝra Māryām
                     “Miracles of Mary”: 123+4 miracles (fols. 20va-176va), incomplete?&#xD; I-5)
                     ʾAkkonu bǝʾsi... "Does not the man..." (fols. 177ra-181rb) &#xD; I-6)
                     Ba-ʾakkʷateta la-ʾab wa-wald wa-manfas qǝddus ʾǝwaṭṭǝn ṣǝḥifä täʾamriha …
                     “Glorifying the father and the son and the holy spirit I begin to write her
                     miracles …” (fol. 183ra-rb)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-7, colophon.</summary>
               </msContents>
